Convicted serial paedophile Bruce Ehrlich who is suing the department of correctional services after his parole was revoked, has filed another application in the Grahamstown High Court. He wants the court to set aside the decision on November 28 by the parole board to deny him parole.Ehrlich was released on parole in 2010 but sent back to prison for breaking parole conditions after he was allegedly seen teaching minor boys squash at the Cambridge Sports Club in East London.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions